### Steps to reproduce

```
<template>
  <div class='root'>
    <button
      @click='open'
      @blur='close'
    >
      btn
    </button>

    <ul class="menu">
      <router-link
        tag='li'
        :to="{ name: 'route' }"
      >
        link
      </router-link>
...
```
```
   .menu {
      display: none;
   }

   .root.active .menu {
      display: block;
    }
```
```
      open() {
        this.$el.classList.toggle('active');
      },

      close() {
        // here. with a delay of approximately 50ms will work as needed
        setTimeout(() => {
          this.$el.classList.remove('active');
        }, 50);
      },
```


### What is expected?
transition

### What is actually happening?
no transition

---
Help to figure out how to be in this situation:
If you remove from dom before the render of the frame in vue is ~ 16ms,
the router-link transition event will be canceled.
$nextTick - did not help out.
@blur.native - does not work.
If you use transparency to hide, everything works.
Maybe it's a bug vue?
